17 was adopted by a United States citizen, and has automatically acquired citizenship in
18 accordance with the federal Child Citizenship Act of 2000 upon the production of the
19 following documents:
20 (1) The child's Certificate of Citizenship;
21 (2) The social security card of the child;
22 (3) A valid government issued form of identification possessing a picture of the parent
23 or parents, such as a passport or driver's license; and
24 (4) Proof of residency of the parent or parents in the State of Georgia.
25 (c) The state registrar shall develop any necessary forms for adoptive parents to submit in
26 order to request a 'Certificate of Foreign Birth.'"
27 SECTION 2.
28 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
